    "id": 29,
    "slug": "disclosure-day-2026",
    "title": "Disclosure Day",
    "year": 2026,
    "director": "Steven Spielberg",
    "poster": "/posters/disclosure-day-2026.jpg",
    "rating": 4,
    "watchedDate": "2026-06-13",
    "review": "Disclosure Day is brilliantly woven and insanely executed. Spielberg's killer craft, as if we needed reminding, is on full display here.\r\n\r\nBut let's talk about the story. Honestly, it tells you almost nothing about its central premise: aliens. And yet it grips you completely. It's the chase. It's good against evil. It's wonder, it's empathy, it's so much heart. That's what makes it such brilliant writing, because when you reveal so little about the aliens, holding an audience is genuinely hard. Spielberg pulls it off not just through how original and alive his characters feel, but through cinematography that floors you. Every shot feels out of this world. Two of my favorites are the one with the deer up top, and the one where the Fruit Loops fall mid-shimmy.\r\n\r\nIt's telling that the film ends on a single word: \"listen.\" What does Spielberg want us to listen to?\r\n\r\nAnd a huge shout-out to the archival footage team. That footage looked so real that, for a second, you genuinely believed what you were seeing could be reality.",
    "tags": null,
    "tmdbId": 1275779,
    "letterboxdUri": "https://boxd.it/MDJY"
  }
